<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612636>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 7. Lateral view of anterior left lower dentition of Marmosops parvidens (A, AMNH 266425) and M. carri (B, KU 120254) illustrating species differences in lower canine (c1) morphology. In M. parvidens, c1 is subequal in height with the first lower premolar (p1), and it has a distinct posterior accessory cusp (pac). By contrast, c1 in M. carri is distinctly taller than p1 and lacks a posterior accessory cusp. Both illustrated specimens are males." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4612636/files/figure.png" .

